24 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 6-13-617 is amended to read as follows:
25 6-13-617. Oath. [Effective May 1, 2024.]
26 (a)(1)(A) Each director shall, within ten (10) days after receiving
27 notice from the county clerk or his or her designee of his or her election or
28 within ten (10) days after receiving notice from the county clerk or his or
29 her designee of his or her appointment, subscribe to the following oath
30 before an individual authorized to administer oaths under § 21-2-105:
31 “I, _____________, do hereby solemnly swear or affirm, that I
32 will support the United States Constitution and the Arkansas Constitution,
33 and that I will not be interested, directly or indirectly, in any contract
34 made by the district of which I am a director, except as permitted by state
35 law, that I shall abide by the ethical guidelines and prohibitions under § 6-
36 24-101 et seq., and that I will faithfully discharge the duties as school
